a$ is finitely connected at the boundary.\n  (6) The completion of $\\Omega$ under the Mazurkiewicz distance is compact.\n\\noindent This provides new generalizations of earlier partial results that are\nrestricted to special cases, when additional assumptions on the topology of $U$\nor its boundary are required.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 20 Feb 2020 09:56:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 30 Mar 2022 08:45:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-09"}
