urity attacks on\ncyber-physical systems, we introduce controller-attacker games (CAG), where two\nplayers, a controller and an attacker, have antagonistic objectives. We\nformulate a special case of CAG called V-formation games, where the attacker's\ngoal is to prevent the controller from attaining V-formation. We demonstrate\nhow adaptation in the design of the controller helps in overcoming certain\nattacks.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 20 Feb 2020 04:00:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-02-24"}
